  "title": "Automation Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Carry out Electrical, Instrumentation, Control and Automation (EICA) design and implementation for construction projects, driving successful project delivery through technical expertise, coordination, and problem resolution.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Design and develop Electrical, Instrumentation, Control and Automation (EICA) systems tailored to construction project requirements</li><li>Manage procurement, costing, and timely delivery of electrical software and hardware to meet project specifications</li><li>Develop and program PLC systems according to clients’ technical specifications, ensuring functional and reliable automation solutions</li><li>Coordinate with contractors to oversee control panel, electrical equipment, and component delivery, ensuring compliance with project timelines and quality standards</li><li>Organize and lead on-site testing and commissioning activities to validate system performance and compliance</li><li>Diagnose and resolve EICA breakdowns promptly to minimize downtime and maintain operational continuity</li><li>Facilitate technical meetings with subcontractors and clients to clarify requirements and coordinate project arrangements</li><li>Maintain systematic records of EICA designs, drawings, and documentation for project tracking and future reference</li><li>Collaborate with Sales Department and Maintenance Team by providing technical support and assistance to enhance project outcomes</li><li>Execute other ad-hoc assignments as required to support project and organizational goals</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Proficient in programming and troubleshooting PLCs including Siemens, Schneider, Allen-Bradley, ABB, and Omron</li><li>Skilled in using SCADA and HMI systems for automation control and monitoring</li><li>Excellent communication skills to effectively liaise with clients, contractors, and internal teams</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s Degree in Engineering (Computer/Telecommunication), Engineering (Electrical/Electronic), or equivalent</li><li>Minimum 3 years of relevant working experience in Electrical, Instrumentation, Control and Automation projects</li></ul>",
